<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="262" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,608]" pageId="5" pageNumber="262">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,332,357]" pageId="5" pageNumber="262">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species can be differentiated from other species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kirkaldy" authorityYear="1900" box="[967,1076,332,356]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Balclutha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="262" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[967,1076,332,356]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="262">Balclutha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the colour pattern, shape of aedeagal base, and curvature of aedeagal shaft. Slight differences are observed among specimens, but whether these represent interspecific variation remains unknown. 
<bibRefCitation box="[795,1071,404,429]" pageId="5" pageNumber="262" refId="ref7315" refString="Webb, M. D. &amp; Vilbaste, J. (1994) Review Of the leafhOpper genus Balclutha Kirkaldy in the Oriental RegiOn (Insecta: HOmOptera: AuchenOrrhyncha: Cicadellidae). Entomologische Abhandlungen Staatliches Museum fur Tierkunde Dresden, 56, 56 - 86." type="journal article">Webb &amp; Vilbaste (1994)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation box="[1128,1305,404,428]" pageId="5" pageNumber="262" refId="ref6606" refString="Lu, L., Zhang, Y. &amp; Webb, M. D. (2013) Review Of the grass feeding leafhOpper genus Balclutha Kirkaldy (Hemiptera: Cicadellidae: DeltOcephalinae) in China. Zootaxa, 3691 (5), 501 - 537. https: // dOi. Org / 10.11646 / zOOtaxa. 3691.5.1" type="journal article">
Lu 
<emphasis box="[1166,1215,404,428]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="262">et al</emphasis>
. (2013)
</bibRefCitation>
recognized that the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="BlOcker" authorityYear="1967" box="[240,368,441,464]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Balclutha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="262" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="punctata">
<emphasis box="[240,368,441,464]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="262">B. punctata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex comprises five valid species (
<taxonomicName authorityName="BlOcker" authorityYear="1967" box="[806,904,441,464]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Balclutha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="262" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="punctata">
<emphasis box="[806,904,441,464]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="262">punctata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis box="[917,1130,440,464]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="262">lineolata arhenana</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis box="[1144,1247,440,463]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="262">tiaowena</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis box="[1260,1358,440,463]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="262">uncinata</emphasis>
) in the 
<collectingRegion box="[151,243,476,501]" country="Oman" name="Shamal ash Sharqiyah" pageId="5" pageNumber="262">Oriental</collectingRegion>
fauna. We interpret the Pakistani specimens examined as all belonging to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="BlOcker" authorityYear="1967" box="[1074,1204,477,500]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Balclutha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="262" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="punctata">
<emphasis box="[1074,1204,477,500]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="262">B. punctata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Based on the figure given by 
<bibRefCitation box="[259,458,511,536]" pageId="5" pageNumber="262" refId="ref6667" refString="MahmOOd, S. H. (1979) A Revision of the leafhoppers (Cicadellidae: Homoptera) of Pakistan andadjoining countries of the Oriental region. Fol. 10. Department Of ZOOlOgy (EntOmOlOgy), University Of Karachi, Karachi, 103 pp." type="book">Mahmood (1979)</bibRefCitation>
this species was previously recorded from 
<collectingCountry box="[957,1052,511,536]" name="Pakistan" pageId="5" pageNumber="262">Pakistan</collectingCountry>
but no information was given by Mahmood on specimens examined. Here we provide the first detailed locality data for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="BlOcker" authorityYear="1967" box="[1155,1372,548,572]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Balclutha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="262" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="punctata">
<emphasis box="[1155,1372,548,572]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="262">Balclutha punctata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[151,246,583,608]" name="Pakistan" pageId="5" pageNumber="262">Pakistan</collectingCountry>
and provide photographs of the habitus.
